{
  "stem": "740.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So for my mother, who was a devout communist and a Bolshevik, it was a way out to go to the west.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They got married.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My father took my mother to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They got married in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He went back to the front lines.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And she stayed with my aunt, my father's sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And as I understand, again, from my father's talking, while she was all by herself, she spoke only Polish and Yiddish, hated the Germans, never learned German, only spoke Yiddish at home, and associated herself with-- the Spartans, in those days, were the Communist party.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Karl Liebknecht, Rosa Luxembourg marched on the streets, shouted against the Kaiser, against the war and all kinds of activities.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In 1918, when my father came back, who was a conservative Democrat, he continued his profession, which was a CPA.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He went to the University of Berlin and made some kind of a degree.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He became a lawyer, a tax lawyer-- what we call today a tax lawyer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And in the meantime, life went on in 1923 with the famous Putsch of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My mother was in the streets yelling, kill the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Kill everybody.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Of course, as a Jewess, that was not the thing to do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The problem arising, that the two entities, my father and my mother, didn't get along emotionally.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So they were fighting every day, like dog and cat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "By 1926, I was born, the little man, which, in a way, was a blessing to both of them, because it gave a little peace in the house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "At that time, my father was very, very busy from 8 o'clock in the morning till 1 o'clock at night, creating new clients, creating money for the household.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
